The numbers between the infected and official recorded may not be consistent. Our model must capture the inconsistency. The counting process C(t1, t2) is the number of officially reported cases between times t1 and t2. The number of people actually infected between times t1 and t2 is ΔNSI(t1, t2). We, therefore, associate the two numbers with relations of proportion and uncertainty in [Eq. (2)].2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
